news.title: SBI hikes MCLR-based lending rates by 10 bps to 7.95-8.70%
news.para: According to the SBI website, the bank has increased the overnight lending rate, based on the marginal cost of funds-based lending rate, by 10 bps to 7.95 per cent, while the same for one-and three-month maturity has been increased to 8.10 per cent.

news.title: MahaRERA to train 39,000 real estate agents in Maharashtra
news.para: ​MahaRERA plans to complete the training, which has been made mandatory for agents, by September, said its nodal officer Sanjay Deshmukh at a session here organised for the first batch of the property agents.

news.title: Gujarat likely to reduce stamp duty, registration fee through finance bill
news.para: Reduction in stamp duty and registration fee has been a long-standing demand of the real estate sector, which has made several representations to the government over this concession.

news.title: New bill likely to replace MOFA under review: Maharashtra cooperation minister
news.para: He said the draft bill would be discussed with all stakeholders before giving the final nod. The new bill deals with conveyance deeds of housing societies not covered under the RERA Act.

news.title: Prevent builders from taking advance maintenance: Mumbai Grahak Panchayat
news.para: It also asked the authority to ensure the formation of cooperative housing societies after more than half the homebuyers have booked flats.

news.title: Jaypee Infratech served notice for green rule violations in Kensington Park 1
news.para: Officials said the show-cause notice was issued after an inspection by the NGT-appointed committee, comprising officials of the district administration and UPPCB, was held on February 3 and a report was submitted to the tribunal on February 10.

news.title: CCI approves acquisition of certain assets of Jaiprakash Associates by Dalmia Cement (Bharat)
news.para: Dalmia Cement (Bharat) is a wholly owned subsidiary of Dalmia Bharat (DBL) which has been in business of the manufacture and sale of cement for over 80 years.

news.title: Brookfield subsidiary defaults on two Los Angeles office buildings
news.para: The two properties, part of Brookfield DTLA Fund Office Trust Investor's portfolio, are 777 Tower and Gas Company Tower, with debts around $290 million and $465 million, respectively.

news.title: MYRE Capital to raise Rs 20 crore through structured debt
news.para: Myre Capital is in the process to apply for the Securities and Exchange Board of India's (SEBI) online bond platform (OBPs) measures.

news.title: Officials inspect Porvorim land for bypass, find it full of buildings
news.para: To ensure there’s no traffic congestion while this road is being built, the government constituted a team comprising representatives of various departments including PWD, panchayats, town and country planning, and land survey, apart from the Goa police’s traffic cell.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: Rs 3 lakh crore offers bagged at GIS, hunt now for land to execute them
news.para: Over the next five years – during which the investments would be made – land would be pooled or acquired mostly in areas off the Yamuna Expressway and the Dadri-Noida-Ghaziabad Investment Region (DNGIR).

news.title: Sebi notifies governance norms for REITs, InvITs similar to listed companies
news.para: This comes after the board of Sebi approved a proposal in December for introducing governance norms for REITs and InvITs on the lines of corporate governance norms for listed companies.

news.title: Residents of Aurangabad's fringe areas forced to assess own properties for tax
news.para: With the local civic body allegedly shying away from its responsibility of bringing the properties under the tax net, a section of citizens claimed that they are now taking help of agents for evaluation of property tax.

news.title: Mumbai's MMRDA to get 91 lakh sq ft saleable area after metro-I takeover: RTI
news.para: MMRDA has a 26% stake in the special purpose vehicle - MMOPL, which runs the Metro I - while Anil Ambani-owned Reliance Infrastructure holds 74%. The 12km corridor between Versova-Andheri-Ghatkopar has 12 stations and a depot at DN Nagar.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 599 properties over property tax default
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed a total of 2,358 properties in the last one week for defaulting on payment of tax despite repeated notices, a statement from the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation said.
